T1  - Goodness of fit for seemingly unrelated regressions: Glahn's R2y.x and Hooper's r̄2
AU  - McElroy, Marjorie B.
JO  - Journal of Econometrics
VL  - 6
IS  - 3
SP  - 381
EP  - 387
PY  - 1977
DA  - 1977/11/01/
SN  - 0304-4076
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-4076(77)90008-2
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304407677900082
AB  - This paper presents a measure of goodness of fit for Zellner's seemingly unrelated regressions. The measure is a monotonic transform of the appropriate (asymptotic) F-statistic, is bounded on [0, 1] and is maximized by Zellner's estimation technique. Glahn's composite correlation coefficient is shown to be a special case of this measure. It is also compared to Hooper's squared trace correlation coefficient. All three measures as well as some additional asymptotic summary test statistics are calculated for the two-equation example of Zellner. The applicability of the latter test statistics seems not to be recognized in applied work.
ER  - 

