UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304407677900070
AB  - The paper formulates a Bayesian test of a parameter shift in two regressions whose error terms have multivariate student-t distributions with zero location vectors. The test is derived first with diffuse and then with natural conjugate prior probability density functions. The Bayesian test is then applied to examine whether or not a parameter shift in expenditure on vitamins and other nutritional supplements can be observed since 1969 in Japan. The empirical test implies that there is a sudden parameter shift in 1971 due to a consumer protection movement.
ER  - 

